DART-atmos-corr

A place for code and tutorials for atmospheric correction of longwave infrared camera imagery using the Discrete Anisotropic Radiative Transfer (DART) model.

This repository is being constantly updated with tutorials and code to give readers of Morrison et al. (2019) (in press) a hands-on guide to performing atmospheric and emissivity corrections for longwave infrared camera imagery across complex terrain.

Summary of atmospheric correction routine

The overall routine is summarised in the below flowchart. Click on a flowchart element to be directed to the appropriate documentation (WIP).

B(Configure Blender model world) > C(Create multi line of sight image) > D(Run DART atmosphere simulation) > E > E > F(Band calculation and correction) > F > G(Analysis) >

A software package has been developed to work with DART outputs: daRt for the R programming language and complements the atmospheric correction processing and analysis. daRt methods are being developed to simplify the atmospheric correction process.
